Plan: Gesture-Based Air Drawing System (Balanced MVP)

Brief TL;DR —
Build a real-time webcam-based air drawing system using MediaPipe Hands and OpenCV in Python. 
Start with a rule-based gesture classification system to achieve a working demo quickly. 
Then extend the system with a lightweight machine learning classifier to improve accuracy and robustness.

Final deliverables:
- Working real-time demo (gesture-based drawing)
- Dataset of hand landmarks
- Simple ML training pipeline
- Evaluation results (rule-based vs ML)
- Final report and documentation

--------------------------------------------------

Steps

1. Requirements Definition
- Define gesture set and behavior
- Define system performance targets
- Document in docs/requirements.md

2. Real-Time MVP (HIGH PRIORITY)
- Capture webcam video using OpenCV
- Detect hand landmarks using MediaPipe Hands
- Implement rule-based gesture classification
- Implement drawing system (canvas + finger tracking)
- Ensure smooth real-time performance

3. Data Collection (AFTER MVP WORKS)
- Capture landmark data with gesture labels
- Store in data/raw/
- Keep dataset small but clean (100–200 samples per gesture)

4. Feature Engineering
- Extract features:
  - Landmark coordinates (x, y)
  - Distances between key points
  - Angles between fingers
- Store processed data in data/processed/

5. Machine Learning Model
- Train simple classifier:
  - Random Forest (recommended)
  OR
  - Small Neural Network (MLP)
- Implement in src/train/

6. Evaluation
- Compare:
  - Rule-based vs ML classifier
- Metrics:
  - Accuracy
  - Response time
- Save results in reports/

7. Final Demo & Improvements
- Add UI improvements (color selection, clear button)
- Add smoothing (reduce flickering)
- Optional: simple GUI (e.g., Streamlit)

