Two-Hand Control Extension (NEW)

Objective: Improve stability and control by requiring an explicit two-hand interaction: the LEFT hand acts as a lock/unlock control, and the RIGHT hand performs drawing and actions only while UNLOCKED.

System Requirements
- Use MediaPipe Hands with `max_num_hands = 2` to detect both hands.
- Identify each hand as `Left` or `Right` using MediaPipe's handedness classification and consistently map logic to the correct physical hand.

Control Logic (LEFT hand)
- LEFT hand = control switch. Only LEFT determines LOCK / UNLOCK.
- OPEN PALM (all fingers up) -> system state = UNLOCK.
- FIST (all fingers down) -> system state = LOCK.
- If LEFT hand is NOT detected -> system MUST remain LOCKED.

Important Rule
- When system state is LOCK -> RIGHT hand must NOT perform ANY action (no drawing, no mode change, no processing).

Action Logic (RIGHT hand)
- Actions operate only when system state == UNLOCK.
- Index finger up only -> DRAW mode.
- Index + middle fingers up -> ERASE mode.
- All fingers down (fist) -> Change color.

Finger Detection Rules
- For index/middle/ring/pinky: finger is UP when fingertip_y < lower_joint_y (remember image origin is top-left).
- Thumb detection: determine thumb-up/left/right by comparing x-axis positions relative to hand orientation (use MediaPipe handedness to interpret direction).

Stability Improvements
- Require frame-based confirmation: a gesture must be observed for at least 5 consecutive frames before confirming and switching modes.
- Add debounce delay between confirmed mode changes: 0.3–0.5 seconds minimum to prevent rapid toggling.

Drawing Logic
- Drawing only occurs in DRAW mode (RIGHT hand) and only while system state is UNLOCK.
- Track previous and current RIGHT-index positions and draw smoothed lines between them (cast to integer pixels for drawing APIs).
- If system becomes LOCKED, immediately stop drawing and freeze canvas state (until unlocked).

Visual Feedback (UI)
- On-screen status: show `LOCKED` (red) or `UNLOCKED` (green) in a visible corner.
- Show current mode label: `DRAW`, `ERASE`, or `SELECT` next to the status.
- Keep existing color swatch and gesture label; add the LOCK/UNLOCK indicator.

Edge Case Handling
- If LEFT hand disappears -> immediately set state to LOCK and ignore RIGHT hand actions.
- If RIGHT hand disappears -> stop drawing (but remain unlocked if LEFT still UNLOCK).
- Only accept RIGHT-hand actions when BOTH conditions are true:
  1. LEFT hand is detected
  2. LEFT hand is in UNLOCK state

Implementation Steps (high level)
1. Update demo to initialize MediaPipe Hands with `max_num_hands=2` and keep handedness info for each detected hand.
2. In the main loop, separate detections into `left_hand` and `right_hand` by checking MediaPipe handedness labels.
3. Implement `fingers_up(hand_landmarks, handedness)` helper that returns bools for each finger using the rules above (thumb logic uses handedness).
4. Add a `frame_confirmation` buffer per logical state (LEFT control state and RIGHT action mode) to accumulate consecutive frames and only confirm after 5 matches.
5. Add a `last_mode_change_ts` timestamp and enforce a 0.3–0.5s lockout between confirmed changes.
6. Wire drawing code to use RIGHT-hand index tip only when confirmed mode == DRAW and system_state == UNLOCK.
7. Add UI rendering for LOCK status and confirmed mode.
8. Test the flow and tune thresholds (frame_count and hold times) for responsiveness and stability.

Acceptance Criteria for Two-Hand Extension
- Left-hand LOCK/UNLOCK reliably controls whether Right-hand actions are accepted.
- Gestures require 5 consecutive frames to confirm; mode switching has the configured debounce delay.
- Drawing only occurs when UNLOCK + confirmed DRAW; if left becomes LOCK, drawing stops immediately.
- UI shows clear LOCK/UNLOCK status and current mode.

